                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13692769" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 25 Jun 2013 05:46:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The grammar suggests that it was intended for semicolon to be optional.  I guess some kind of antlr nondeterminism makes it not work as designed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13692808" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 25 Jun 2013 07:19:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The semicolon is optional. You are getting this error because cqlsh splits its statements internally. Using python-cql directly (or any other client), the semicolons will be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s questionable whether or not messing with cqlsh internals just to allow the semicolons in BATCH is worth it, but I&apos;ll have a look later today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13702340" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 8 Jul 2013 19:53:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13702391" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 8 Jul 2013 20:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
